OL,6,FA statement on the club's website
OL,7,Fsaid: "A man mountain on the pitch and
OL,8,Fa gentleman off it, Charlie's aura and
OL,9,Fcharisma ensured that he was adored
OL,10,Fand idolised by supporters and team-
OL,11,Fmates alike.
OL,13,F"Charlie adored Sunderland and
OL,14,FSunderland will always adore him. Our
OL,15,Fheartfelt sympathies are with his
OL,16,Ffamily, and all who loved him."
OL,18,FBorn in Cork and raised in London,
OL,19,FHurley began his career at Millwall in
OL,20,F1953, joining Sunderland four years
OL,21,Flater.
