OL,3,CSunderland and Ireland legend Charlie
OL,4,C'The King' Hurley dies aged 87
OL,6,FHe made his international debut at the
OL,7,Fage of 20 in 1-1 draw with England in
OL,8,FDublin in 1957. He went on to captain
OL,9,Fhis country on more than 20 occasions.
OL,11,FHis final appearance for Sunderland
OL,12,Fcame in 1969 and he then departed for
OL,13,Fa short spell at Bolton Wanderers
OL,14,Fbefore hanging up his boots.
OL,16,FHowever, he would make an emotional
OL,17,Freturn to Roker Park as manager of
OL,18,FReading, when the Royals were drawn
OL,19,Faway at Sunderland during their FA Cup
OL,20,Fwinning campaign of 1973.
