OL,6,FHurley's final visit to the Stadium of
OL,7,FLight came during celebrations for his
OL,8,F80th birthday in 2016, when players
OL,9,Fincluding Cecil Irwin, Len Ashurst,
OL,10,FMartin Harvey, Brian Usher, George
OL,11,FHerd, Stan Anderson and Jimmy
OL,12,FMontgomery came together in honour of
OL,13,Ftheir former captain.
OL,15,FThe Charlie Hurley gates which had
OL,16,Fonce formed the entrance to the Club's
OL,17,Ftraining ground, were given a
OL,18,Fpermanent home in the grounds of the
OL,19,FStadium of Light.
