OL,6,FFootball Association of Ireland
OL,7,Fpresident Paul Cooke said: "Our
OL,8,Fthoughts and prayers are with Charlie
OL,9,FHurley's family and friends at this
OL,10,Fdifficult time.
OL,12,F"It is over 50 years since Charlie won
OL,13,Fthe last of his 40 caps, but it is a
OL,14,Fmeasure of the esteem in which he was
OL,15,Fheld in football that every Irish fan
OL,16,Fknows of the legend that was Charlie
OL,17,FHurley.
OL,19,F"We are proud that he played for
OL,20,FIreland and we extend our deepest
OL,21,Fsympathies to all who knew The King."
